A Caesarean section, (also C-section, Caesarian section, Cesarean section, Caesar, etc.) is a surgical procedure in which one or more incisions are made through a mother's abdomen (laparotomy) and uterus (hysterotomy) to deliver one or more babies, or, rarely, to remove a dead fetus. A late-term abortion using Caesarean section procedures is termed a hysterotomy abortion and is very rarely performed. The first modern Caesarean section was performed by German gynecologist Ferdinand Adolf Kehrer in 1881.

A Caesarean section is usually performed when a vaginal delivery would put the baby's or mother's life or health at risk, although in recent times it has also been performed upon request for childbirths that could otherwise have been natural. In recent years the rate has risen to a record level of 46% in China and to levels of 25% and above in many Asian, European and Latin American countries. In 2007, in the United States, the Caesarean section rate was 31.8%. Across Europe, there are significant differences between countries: in Italy the Caesarean section rate is 40%, while in the Nordic countries it is only 14%. Medical professional policy makers find that elective cesarean can be harmful to the fetus and neonate without benefit to the mother, and have established strict guidelines for non-medically indicated cesarean before 39 weeks.

Source: Wikipedia

As the rest of Europe watched on, Russia was booed a number of times during the Eurovision Song Contest tonight.
When the country "phoned in" to deliver its top three votes, the crowd could be heard booing the Russian spokesman as she attempted to read out the country's results from Moscow.

After Russia delivered its vote -- giving a full 12 points to neighbouring Belarus, 10 to Azerbaijan and eight to Armenia -- the crowd could still be heard booing.

Countries who voted for Russia, including Armenia and Belarus, were also booed when delivering points to the country, which has been at the centre of criticism over its handling of the crisis in Ukraine and its controversial anti-gay propaganda law.

Russia's entry, the identical Tolmachevy twins, were also booed during the first Eurovision semi-final on Tuesday

description:
The housefly is the most common of all domestic flies, accounting for about 91% of all flies in human habitations, and indeed one of the most widely distributed insects, found all over the world. Houseflies are believed to have evolved in the beginning of the Cenozoic era, some 65 million years ago. It is considered a pest that can carry serious diseases. They are capable of carrying over 100 pathogens, such as those causing typhoid, cholera, salmonellosis, bacillary dysentery, tuberculosis, anthrax, ophthalmia, and parasitic worms. (in assamese - মধ্যবক্ষত এযোৰ পাখি আৰু পিছৰ পাখিযোৰ ৰূপান্তৰিত হৈ এযোৰ শুং থকা, দিপ্টেৰা বৰ্গৰ পতঙ্গসমূহ ৷ সাধাৰণতে দেখা পোৱা ঘৰুৱা মাখিবোৰেই হ'ল প্ৰকৃত মাখি আৰু ইহঁত পৃথিৱীৰ আটাইতকৈ বহলভাৱে বিস্তৃত প্ৰাণীবোৰৰ অন্যতম ৷)
Each female fly can lay approximately 500 eggs in several batches of about 75 to 150. The eggs are white and are about 1.2 mm in length. Within a day, larvae (maggots) hatch from the eggs; they live and feed on (usually dead and decaying) organic material, such as garbage or feces. They live at least one week. The adults live from two weeks to a month in the wild, or longer in benign laboratory conditions. Some 36 hours after having emerged from the pupa, the female is receptive for mating. Copulation takes a few seconds to a couple of minutes. Normally, the female mates only once, storing the sperm to use it repeatedly for laying several sets of eggs. The flies depend on warm temperatures; generally, the warmer the temperature, the faster the flies will develop. In colder climates, houseflies survive only with humans.
Although they are domestic flies, usually confined to human habitations, they can fly for several miles from the breeding place. They are active only in daytime, and rest at night, e.g., at the corners of rooms, ceiling hangings, cellars, and barns, where they can survive the coldest winters by hibernation, and when spring arrives, adult flies are seen only a few days after the first thaw.
title: Housefly are capable of carrying over 100 pathogens (in Assamese - মাখি)

The primrose is distinguished from other species of Primula by its pale yellow (in the nominate subspecies) flowers produced singly on long flower stalks which are covered in rather shaggy hairs. The flowers open flat rather than concave as in the case of Primula veris, the Cowslip. Both flowers and leaves are edible, the flavour ranging between mild lettuce and more bitter salad greens. The leaves can also be used for tea, and the young flowers can be made into primrose wine. See more: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primula_vulgaris

description:
"Si he pecado por pintarlo pido perdón, pero no he podido terminarlo"
Cecilia, la vecina de Borja que llevaba varios años restaurando el 'Ecce Homo' de la iglesia, ha pedido perdón por su obra, aunque se ha lamentado por no poder terminarla. La prensa internacional y las redes sociales también se han hecho eco de la noticia.
Cecilia es posiblemente uno de los personajes más buscados hoy en nuestro país. Es la octogenaria vecina de Borja, en Zaragoza que, en un gesto de buena voluntad, decidió restaurar por su cuenta una pintura del s.XIX.

Ella lo hizo con su mejor intención, pero lo cierto es que el resultado es más que discutible. Un equipo de restauradores profesionales se va a hacer cargo de esa obra para intentar que recupere en lo posible su aspecto original. La mujer, de hecho, se ha ofrecido ya a colaborar con ellos.

Está previsto que el próximo lunes esta espontánea restauradora se reúna con este equipo de profesionales. A ellos les va a explicar los materiales utilizados para obtener este sorprendente resultado.

Cecilia lleva años restaurándola y nadie se lo había prohibido. Dice que la obra todavía está por terminar. Sin duda se ha convertido en un atractivo turístico para el pequeño municipio de Borja.

Cecilia, de 80 años, se encuentra muy afectada por lo sucedido: "Si yo he pecado por pintarlo, pido perdón, pero lo he hecho con muy buena intención". No deja de repetir que no ha podido terminar su trabajo. "No me arrepiento de querer arreglarlo, pero no he podido terminarlo".

"Sé pintar. Desde pequeña en el colegio he hecho exposiciones y he vendido muchos cuadros", asegura Cecilia. Teresa García, la nieta del verdadero autor de la obra no le guarda rencor: "Le doy todo mi apoyo, es una señora muy mayor. Estaba la pobre muy disgustada".

En la calle, el debate social continúa. "No hay derecho. Si se hubiera hecho antes no se hubiera llegado a esta situación", cree una vecina. "Yo tengo cuadros de ella en mi casa y están muy bien. Algo le ha pasado", afirma otra vecina de Borja.

Hoy el muro del templo es casi un lugar de peregrinación. Todos quieren comprobar con sus propios ojos el antes y el después del famoso Cristo de Borja.

Repercusión en las redes sociales
Como ya es habitual en este tipo de casos, la historia del fresco de la iglesia de Borja no ha dejado impasible a nadie. La prensa internacional se ha hecho eco del asunto y las redes sociales se han volcado.

De "masacre" califica en su portada el diario francés Le Monde lo ocurrido en la iglesia de Borja. Un asunto que también recoge el británico Daily Telegraph.

En la red, la noticia ha corrido como la pólvora. En Twitter, el 'Ecce mono' ya es Trending Topic. "Hola amigos, bienvenidos a Bricomanía. Hoy vamos a ver como restaurar un 'Ecce homo' del s.XIX", "Ahora ya no sé si mi hijo me hace dibujos o se dedica a restaurar 'Ecce Homo' en secreto" y "Hola, soy la restauradora del 'Ecce Homo'. Aquí os dejo un adelanto de mi próxima restauración, 'La Gioconda'" son algunos de los tweets que se han hecho eco de la restauración.

En Facebook se han creado varios grupos donde no cesan los comentarios: "De la creadora de 'Las Caras de Bélmez', llega 'Ecce Homo'". Avispados comerciantes en menos de 24 horas han puesto a la venta camisetas con la nueva imágen.

Lo cierto es que ya se cuentan por cientos las hilarantes versiones de la pintura aparecidas en la red en las últimas horas. Personajes reales y ficticios, obras de arte, cantantes, nobles... Nadie puede escapar a la creatividad de los internautas.
title: HABLA LA RESTAURADORA DEL "ECCE HOMO"

description:
2013 Collegiate Inventors Competition Finalist - Undergraduate
Piyush Poddar, Sandya Subramanian, Kevin George, Aaron Chang
Johns Hopkins University
The PrestoPatch 
Advisor: Robert Allen

The PrestoPatch Integrated Electrode System allays the two major shortcomings of cardiac arrhythmia treatment: 1) Difficulty in switching the shocking vector (path the shock takes through the body) between shocks 2) Difficulty in applying standardized external pressure to the patches to reduce transthoracic impedance (resistance to the electrical shock). The PrestoPatch system saves lives by solving these problems via two separate components: 1) The Tri-Patch, a disposable three-patch electrode that allows for a instantaneously switchable shocking vector 2) The PrestoPush, an ergonomic, hand-held pressure applicator that can quickly reduce transthoracic impedance on all electrode patches.
title: PrestoPatch  - First Prize, Undergrad - Collegiate Inventors Competition 2013

description:
******IF YOU LIKE PLEASE SUBSCRIBE*****

And so the ridiculousness continues...multiplies even.  I thought I would try this.  There's at least a couple really great covers of this song already out on the Youtubes.  One was made by three kids in a stairwell and it was awesome.  One was done by my sister-in-law with her friends with a melodica and it was also awesome.

I have no idea what possessed me to do this, save for that I was kind of impressed with my work on Holiday, and I've been listening to the Fleet Foxes' CD recently.  I wanted to do more things with multiples of myself, and I could think of too many other songs with three part harmony...too many others that I could reasonably perform at least.

Overall I was shocked how well this worked, and how nice the animated mask on my foot is (in the very beginning of the video you can actually see the middle guy kick his foot in front of the guitar on the right).  It's a small thing but it really completes the video.

As for the quality of the music, I know there are some mistakes, and the mandolin was hideously out of tune, but really the guitar and vocals cover it up.  I'm actually quite happy with how it came out.  I really don't know whether or not what I'm doing is really going to work until I get it into the computer.  I was floored by how well this one worked.  Perhaps it will be incentive to keep working on this stuff.  Granted, making covers means I'm not making my own music...but hey, at least it's fun right?

Thanks for commenting, subscribing and more!

description:
Heilpflanzen / Ziest-Arten

Waldziest (Stachys sylvatica L.) Waldnessel
Sumpfziest (Stachys palustris L.) Schweinerübe


Waldziest (Stachys sylvatica L.)

Pflanzennamen im Volksmund
Waldziest, Waldnessel
Sumpfziest: Schweinerübe

Wissenschaftlicher Name
Waldziest: Stachys sylvatica L.
Sumpfziest: Stachys palustris L.

Pflanzenfamilie
Lippenblütler (Lamiaceae)

Heilkräuter / Anwendung
Krämpfe, Menstruation, Ohrensausen, Wechseljahre.
Steckbrief / Beschreibung

Waldziest und Sumpfziest sind kräftige Pflanzen, die in fast allen Ländern Europas weit verbreitet sind. Der aus dem griechischen stammende Gattungsname Stachys bedeutet Ähre und deutet auf die Form des Blütenstandes hin. Wie der Name vermuten lässt, findet man den Waldziest mit seinen purpurroten Blüten in Laub- und Mischwäldern. Hier ist die Pflanze weit verbreitet. Waldziest riecht unangenehm nach Wanzen. Der Sumpfziest wächst entlang von Gräben und auf feuchten Ackerböden. Der Sumpfziest bildet rosa bis rotviolette, weiß gefleckte Blüten. Beide Ziest-Arten erreichen eine Wuchshöhe von etwa 1 m. Die Pflanzen werden gerne von Schafen und Ziegen abgeweidet, ihre Blüten von Bienen und Hummeln besucht. Die knollig verdickten Bodenausläufer des Sumpfziests verwendetet man früher in einigen Gegenden als Ersatz für den eigentlichen Knollenziest (S. sieboldii Miq.) zu Nahrungszwecken genutzt.

In der Naturheilkunde werden Wald- und Sumpfziest nur noch selten verwendet. Beide Ziest-Arten besitzen krampflösende Eigenschaften, der Waldziest wirkt außerdem menstruationsregulierend, der Sumpfziest harntreibend. Beide Ziest-Arten sind ausdauernde Pflanzen, je nach Standort erreichen sie eine Wuchshöhe von 40 bis 120 cm. Die Stängel der Pflanzen sind beblättert und behaart.

Waldziest: Die grün gefärbten und gestielt wachsenden Blätter des Waldziests sind herzförmig, die Blattränder sind gesägt. Die sich in drei- bis sechsblütigen Scheinquirlen bilden Blüten des Waldziests haben eine dunkel purpurrote Färbung.

Sumpfziest: Beim Sumpfziest wachsen die unteren Blätter kurz gestielt, die Blätter im oberen Bereich der Pflanze sind sitzend. Die Blattform ist länglich-lanzettlich, die Blattränder sind gesägt. Die sich in vier- bis achtblütigen Scheinquirlen bilden Blüten des Sumpfziest haben eine dunkel rosa Färbung mit weißen Flecken.
Standort / Hier findet man den Ziest

Der Waldziest wächst im gesamten europäischen Raum. Im Mittelmeerraum sind die Pflanzen jedoch nur sehr selten zu finden. Als Standort bevorzugt der Waldziest nicht allzu trockene Wälder.

Der Sumpfziest wächst, mit Ausnahme des Mittelmeerraumes ebenfalls im gesamten Europa. Sumpfziest bevorzugt feuchtere Standorte als der Waldziest. Gewöhnlich findet man diese Pflanze in dauerfeuchten Gräben und auch an Flussufern.
Wirkung der Heilpflanze / Heilwirkung - Ziest

Waldziest: krampflösend, reguliert die Menstruation, sedativ Sumpfziest: krampflösend, harntreibend
In der Naturheilkunde verwendete Pflanzenteile

In der Naturheilkunde benutzt man von dem Waldziest und auch von dem Sumpfziest die blühenden Sprossspitzen. Der Sammelzeitraum erstreckt sich vom Juni bis in den September.
Anwendung mit der Heilkraft dieser Pflanze

Der Ziest wird in der Pflanzenheilkunde innerlich angewendet. Anwendungen mit den Ziest-Arten in der Naturheilkunde finden Sie unter folgenden Stichworten:

Krämpfe, Menstruation, Ohrensausen, Wechseljahre
Bitte beachten Sie auch diesen Hinweis

Obwohl die Anwendungen mit Heilkräutern oft eine positive Wirkung auf Beschwerden haben, sollte man vor der Heilpflanzenanwendung immer Rücksprache mit einem Arzt halten. Dies gilt auch für Anwendungen mit dem Sumpf- und Waldziest.
title: Ziest-Arten. Waldziest, Waldnessel. Sumpfziest: Schweinerübe

For more info about eosinophilic esophagitis, visit our website: http://www.vocalhealth.org/disorders/dysphagia/causes/eosinophilic-esophagitis/
Visit our FaceBook page for Singers: http://www.fb.com/SingWellVSI
Follow us on Twitter: http://twitter.com/singwellvsi

Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. When they build up in the esophagus—usually as a reaction to foods or allergens—they can cause inflammation of the esophagus, which in turn can cause food to become stuck there.  It often presents in patients between the ages of 20 and 40.

Patients complain of food intermittently getting stuck in the esophagus. It could last a few minutes or a few hours. Often patients have gone to the ER to get the food removed. Many patients otherwise generally swallow without difficulty and have histories of significant allergy symptoms.
title: EOSINOPHILIC ESOPHAGITIS: PRESENTATION VIDEO

description:
What can we expect to experience when travelling at hyperspeed to our nearest star. Time is experienced differently and the journey's time is radically different to that experienced by those on Earth.

About Proxima Centauri:

Proxima Centauri (Latin proxima, meaning "next to" or "nearest to") is a red dwarf about 4.24 light-years from the Sun, inside the G-cloud, in the constellation of Centaurus. It was discovered in 1915 by Scottish astronomer Robert Innes, the Director of the Union Observatory in South Africa, and is the nearest known star to the Sun, although it is too faint to be seen with the naked eye, with an apparent magnitude of 11.05. Its distance to the second- and third-nearest stars, which form the bright binary Alpha Centauri, is 0.237 ± 0.011 ly (15,000 ± 700 AU). Proxima Centauri is very likely part of a triple star system with Alpha Centauri A and B.

Because of the proximity of this star, its distance from the Sun and angular diameter can be measured directly, from which it can be determined that its diameter is about one-seventh of that of the Sun. Proxima Centauri's mass is about an eighth of the Sun's, and its average density is about 40 times that of the Sun. Although it has a very low average luminosity, Proxima is a flare star that undergoes random dramatic increases in brightness because of magnetic activity. The star's magnetic field is created by convection throughout the stellar body, and the resulting flare activity generates a total X-ray emission similar to that produced by the Sun. The mixing of the fuel at Proxima Centauri's core through convection and the star's relatively low energy-production rate suggest that it will be a main-sequence star for another four trillion years, or nearly 300 times the current age of the universe.

description:
Working Toward Proper Groundwater Branding

Groundwater is the main raw material in mineral water, soft drinks, alcoholic beverages, and food processing. It is a natural resource that can be sustainably supplied at low cost with proper quality control. It is very important to identify the water source and determine the quality of its properties.
Recently, falsification of the origin of food products has become a source of public concern. Information about groundwater sources, such as where they are and how deep or extensive they are, is now being requested by the public.
We have developed a technology that uses a combination of different methods for increased effectiveness. It is now possible to identify the source of groundwater scientifically by analyzing its stable isotopic ratios and major dissolved ion concentrations and by conducting numerical simulations based on satellite images and geomorphic analysis.
title: MMTEC Determining the source of groundwater by analyzing isotopes

description:
Cutting bright green flesh Kiwi fruit Ultra HD 4K - Kiwifruit is native to northern China. Other species of Actinidia are native to India, Japan, and southeastern Siberia.

Cultivation of the fuzzy kiwifruit spread from China in the early 20th century to New Zealand, where the first commercial plantings occurred. The fruit was called "yang tao", but was changed to "Chinese gooseberry" by the New Zealanders.It proved popular with American servicemen in New Zealand during World War II. Because of this, the fruit was exported to California using the names "Chinese gooseberry" and "melonette". Because the California-based importer rejected these names, the fruit was rebranded "kiwifruit" because of its resemblance to the New Zealand kiwi bird.

Kiwifruit has since become a common name for all commercially grown fruit from the genus Actinidia.

Almost all kiwifruit sold belong to a few cultivars of fuzzy kiwi (Actinidia deliciosa): 'Hayward', 'Blake', and 'Saanichton 12'.They have a fuzzy, dull-brown skin, and bright-green flesh. The familiar cultivar 'Hayward' was developed by Hayward Wright in Avondale, New Zealand, around 1924.It was initially grown in domestic gardens, but commercial planting began in the 1940s.

'Hayward' is the most commonly available cultivar in stores. It is a large, egg-shaped fruit with a sweet flavor. 'Saanichton 12', from British Columbia, is somewhat more rectangular than 'Hayward' and comparably sweet, but the inner core of the fruit can be tough. 'Blake' can self-pollinate, but it has a smaller, more oval fruit and the flavor is considered inferior.

description:
On July 3, 2013, Craves Brothers Farmstead Cheese Company of Waterloo, Wisconsin recalled three cheeses for potential Listeria contamination after the company's cheese products were identified as the source of a Listeria outbreak.  
According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, at least 5 people from 4 states fell ill with Listeria infections after eating Craves Brothers brand cheeses. One person died and all others were hospitalized due to their illnesses. One woman suffered a miscarriage as a result of her Listeria infection.
Symptoms of Listeria infection include fever, severe headache, stiffness, nausea, abdominal pain and diarrhea. Symptoms are typically more serious in frail or elderly people, and others with compromised immune systems. Pregnant women infected with Listeria can suffer miscarriage or give birth to stillborn babies.
The recalled cheeses were distributed nationwide through retail and foodservice outlets as well as by mail order.  Both Whole Foods and Kroger stores initiated their own recalls of Craves Brothers cheeses after learning of the potential Listeria risk.

For more information, please visit:
http://www.marlerclark.com/craves-brothers-listeria-cheese-outbreak-lawyer/
http://www.about-listeria.com/
title: Crave Farms Cheese Listeria Outbreak and Recall

description:
The troubled U.S. homeland missile defense program, heavily criticized for its unreliability, has finally carried out a successful test.
The system, deployed ten years ago by former president George W Bush, is supposed to counter the long-range missile threat posed by North Korea.
Shin Se-min has more. 
The U.S. missile defense system on Sunday struck down a simulated enemy missile over the Pacific in the first successful intercept test of the program since 2008.
This will help validate the troubled Boeing-run Ground-based Midcourse Defense system which provides the sole U.S. defense against long-range ballistic missiles.
Missile Defense Agency Director Vice Admiral James Syring called it a very important step in Washington's continuing efforts to improve and increase the reliability of the defense system.
The Pentagon also said all components involved in the test performed as planned,... and the officials will be assessing the performance of the system with the data collected from the test. 

The system had failed to hit dummy missiles in previous tests since the Bush administration deployed the system in 2004 to counter the threat posed by North Korea. 
It was reported on Friday that the Pentagon had restructured its contract with Boeing to put more emphasis on maintenance and reliability. 
Shin Se-min, Arirang News.
title: U.S. missile defense system hits target in key test

www.vientianetimes.org.la

His Imperial Highness the Crown Prince of Japan arrived in Vientiane yesterday on his first official visit to Laos.

Crown Prince Naruhito is paying a three-day official visit to Laos from June 29 to July 1, in response to an invitation from President Choummaly Sayasone, a press release from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said. 

The visit is the highest level visit ever made by Japan's Imperial Family to Laos, since the two countries established diplomatic relations in 1955.

An official welcoming ceremony was held at the Presidential Palace for the Crown Prince and his delegation shortly after their chartered aircraft landed at Wattay International Airport yesterday morning.

Vice President Bounnhang Vorachit led a high-ranking Lao delegation to welcome Crown Prince Naruhito and his delegation. Shortly after the two stood to attention for the national anthems of Japan and Laos, Mr Bounnhang accompanied the prince to inspect a guard of honour.

In talks after the welcoming ceremony, the vice president expressed his warmest welcome to the prince and his delegation. The two highly valued the traditional relations and growing cooperation between Laos and Japan.

Lao leaders and members of the Imperial Family of Japan have exchanged visits over the years, the press release said.

President Choummaly Sayasone paid an official visit to Japan in March 2010 when the two countries marked the 55th anniversary of diplomatic relations. He also met Japan's Emperor Akihito. In the same year, His Imperial Highness Prince Akishino and his daughter Mako visited Laos.

Mr Bounnhang said he highly valued the visit of the Crown Prince. The visit would enhance the close contact and mutual understanding between high-level leaders of Laos and the Imperial Family of Japan, he said, as well as understanding between the two peoples.

The Lao leader expressed hope that the visit of the prince would promote greater investment by the Japanese private sector in Laos.

Laos has received enormous assistance from the government and people of Japan.

The Japanese government provides about US$80 million in official development assistance (ODA) to Laos every year on average, making Japan Laos's single largest ODA provider, according to the Ministry of Planning and Investment.

On the same day, the prince received a courtesy visit from the President of the Laos-Japan Friendship Association, Dr Ponmek Dalaloy, the press release said.

The Crown Prince also met with Prime Minister Thongsing Thammavong. The Lao premier expressed his great appreciation for the cooperation and mutual assistance through bilateral and multilateral frameworks, as well as in the regional arena.

On behalf of the Lao government and people, Mr Thongsing expressed his gratitude to the government and people of Japan for the valuable assistance and support they have extended to Laos, especially in hosting the upcoming 9th Asia-Europe Meeting Summit.

He expressed his appreciation to the Crown Prince for the manner in which the two countries have supported one another in the regional and international arenas.

Later, the Crown Prince met with President Choummaly Sayasone. The president said he highly valued the visit of the prince to Laos, which he said was significant in further strengthening the bilateral relations between Laos and Japan.

The president said such visits would promote mutual understanding between the two peoples and believed it would encourage more Japanese to invest in and visit Laos.

For his part, the Crown Prince thanked the Lao government and people for the warm welcome extended to him and his delegation. He also thanked the Lao people for the relief assistance they provided to victims of the tsunami that devastated Japan in early 2011.

The two spoke highly of the growing bilateral friendly relations and cooperation between Laos and Japan.
The Lao president then hosted a banquet in honour of Japan's Crown Prince and his delegation, which was attended by high-level officials from both sides.
title: Japan's Crown Prince makes landmark visit to Laos

description: From VOA Learning English, this is the Economics Report in Special English. Corruption, like bribery, abuse of power and secret dealings are still "very high" in many countries. This week (December 5, 2012) Transparency International released its yearly Corruption Perceptions Index. The Berlin-based group rates 176 countries and territories with a number from 100 to zero. Bigger numbers are better. The index measures the perceived, or apparent, level of corruption in a country. The group uses information from the African Development Bank, the World Bank and the World Economic Forum. Corruption takes many forms. Transparency International calls it "the abuse of entrusted power for private gain." One common form is bribery: the use of money or gifts to persuade another person to do something wrong or illegal. Corruption is not easy to measure because it is secretive. But the World Bank has estimated that about $1 trillion in bribes are paid every year worldwide. Stealing public money is another form of corruption. Huguette Labelle is chair of Transparency International. She says the problem of corruption affects millions of people and limits their ability to get essential services like water, education, health, and licenses. A group of small, developed nations scored highest on the new list. Denmark, Finland and New Zealand received a rating of 90. Among large nations, the United States rated 73 while China rated 39. The countries with the greatest perceived level of corruption on the list are Somalia, North Korea and Afghanistan with scores of 8. Robin Hodess directs research at Transparency International. She says transparency international needs evidence about how corruption works, and needs to know where to target the reforms needed to promote accountability and integrity." The perceptions held by experts, businesses and organizations are important. The World Bank notes that countries showing improvements had greater foreign investment and economic growth. For VOA Learning English, I'm Carolyn Presutti.
title: Corruption Index Released

About USA Basketball
Based in Colorado Springs, Colo., USA Basketball is a nonprofit organization and the national governing body for men's and women's basketball in the United States. As the recognized governing body for basketball in the U.S. by the International Basketball Federation (FIBA) and the United States Olympic Committee (USOC), USA Basketball is responsible for the selection, training and fielding of USA teams that compete in FIBA sponsored international competitions, as well as for some national competitions.

During the 2009-12 quadrennium, 1,273 men and women players and 235 coaches participated in USA Basketball, including USA Basketball Teams, USA Basketball trials and the USA Basketball 3x3 FIBA championships.

USA Basketball men's and women's teams between 2009-12 compiled an impressive 264-35 win-loss record in FIBA and FIBA Americas competitions, the Pan American Games, the World University Games, the Nike Hoop Summit and in exhibition games. 

USA teams are the current men's and women's champions in the Olympics; men's and women's FIBA World Championships (Basketball World Cup); men's and women's FIBA U19 World Championship; men's and women's FIBA U17 World Championships; men's and women's U18 and U16 FIBA Americas Championships, and FIBA 3x3 Women's World Championship and FIBA 3x3 Women's U18 World Championship.  USA Basketball also currently ranks No. 1 in all five of FIBA's world ranking categories, including combined, men's, women's, boys and girls.

description:
The National Association of Home Builders conducted a large survey this month:  What do Homebuyers want?  Efficiency, Amenities, and Technology. The number one thing buyers want is Energy-star rated appliances. This was followed closely by energy efficiency in the laundry room.  Permanently lowering utility bills is a highly desirable feature. 
Of those polled, 62 percent favored high-quality products over space. Home buyers seem to prefer high-end amenities, even if it means living in a smaller home to get them.. bye bye McMansion. 
Some of the other desired amenities toping their list? were double sinks in the kitchen, a tub and shower stall in the bath. The last thing buyers want: technology: everything from remotely controlled utilities, entertainment to security systems. 
On the flip side, what DON'T homebuyers want? An elevator is the number one amenity consumers don't want, followed closely by wine refrigerators, golf course communities, and outdoor kitchens. 
All good things to keep in mind when buying or renovating. Follow me on Twitter @WoodworthCourt for all your #realestate and business news. For the Financial News Network Online, I'm Courtney Woodworth.
title: What Amenities Do Homebuyers Really Want?

We were born at night when the she-wolf whelped,

There is no god but Allah

Our mothers raised us to dedicate ourselves to our Nation and our Homeland,

There is no god but Allah

There is no god but Allah

Sooner will cliffs of granite begin to melt like molten lead,
Than any one of us shall lose our honour in life's struggles.
There is no god but Allah

There is no god but Allah

Never to bow our heads to anyone, we give our sacred pledge,
To die or to live in freedom is our fate.
There is no god but Allah
Our sisters heal our brothers' bloody wounds with their songs,
Lovers' eyes will supply the strength of arms.
There is no god but Allah

If hunger weaken us, we'll gnaw on the roots of trees,
And if thirst debilitates us, we'll drink the dew from the grass.
There is no god but Allah
For we were born at night when the she-wolf whelped.
We pledge our lives to God, Nation and Vainakh homeland.
There is no god but Allah

Beceause of the single pivot I had to make double layers. The frame only hangs on one screw, this way the escapement can be easily tuned by slightly rotating the whole model. The Canadian Badlands and Dinosaur Provincial Park is one of the largest concentrations of dinosaur bones in the world.  They are EVERYWHERE!

If you think you've found a fossil, or want to make sure the fossil you're about to buy is legit, there's an easy test - the lick test.  Lick your finger, touch the fossil and if it sticks, like on a piece of tape, it's a fossil.  If it pulls away without clinging, it's just a rock.
title: The Lick Test: How To Find Dinosaur Bones And Fossils

This is my 1 1/2 year old micro system at office.
The only nutrients are from fish food and a "soup" made from dried Symphytum officinale and Urtica dioica leaves.
Water pump runs 15 min. an hour, air pump runs 27/7 
Water pump - Aquael Fan Mini plus
Light - 2x39W T5 HO 865 Osram runs 10 h / day (light tubes must be replaced)
Fish  - Endler guppy (Poecilia wingei)
Plans - Capsicum annum + Ocimum basilicum + Petroselinum crispum + Levisticum officinale, all planted in November (2 months old)
Gravel - 6 mm aquarium gravel

PS You can see one poor fish is very ill. Actually there are two in the tank, don't know what their illness is, but the other ones seems to be healthy. The ill ones are like this for about 3 months now (they are getting thiner though) and i could not see other fish getting ill but them. :|

I really don't know whether this video is any good or not but the idea came to me and I thought I would run with it. I am not to sure about the ending in particular and some of the editing is not how I want it to be. Anyway please tell me 
what you think I hope someone likes it lol Please Rate And Comment it means a lot to me thanks xx

The relationship between King Henry and Anne Boleyn was one that involved many different things. They really did love each other but sadly there were many other factors and people that meant in the end it ended very tragically. Many will think that this was because Henry was so worried about Anne not giving him a son but truthfully I think this was only a small part. Anne hated that Henry had so many affairs, and who wouldn't after 7 years of him being totally devoted to only her, and she just was not the average kind of woman of her time. She was not afraid to say what she really felt, she had opinions of her own on subjects that were usually reserved only for men and she loved her husband just that little bt to much and was unable to turn her head away when he strayed because he truly broke her heart. Anyway in this video I hoped that I could get across some of the happy things about their relationship aswell as the sad. And anyway no matter how much Henry hurt and humiliated Anne, as it says in the video, she had her final victory because it was her daughter who went onto became a truly formidable Queen.

Disclaimer: I own nothing...this was done only for entertainment thanks
title: The Love of Anne Boleyn and King Henry VIII - Greensleeves (The Tudors)

Sainik School Bijapur- Grand Teachers' Day Celebrations,
05 Sept 2013
Teachers' Day was celebrated at Sainik School Bijapur in a grand Scale. Prof MB Kudari, retired professor of English from JSS college,Gokak was the chief guest. In his address to students and staff at Sainik School, Bijapur, he recalled the life of Dr. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan (1888-1975), former President of India, as most erudite of Hindu scholars of all times a philosopher, author, statesman and educationalist. He served as India's Vice-President (1952-1962) and later as President (1962-1967).He called upon students' to emulate ideals of Dr. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan. Col R Balaji, Principal thanked Prof MB Kudari, retired professor of English for enlightening on the life of Dr. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan. Earlier, Shri PM Shetty, Master in English introduced Prof MB Kudari, retired professor of English to the audience.
Later in the day, students of class XII, with support of Class XI organised multiple games to entertain teachers. The games were very interesting and teachers' participated enthusiastically. Teachers won prizes for winning in the events. The celebration of teachers' day concluded with special lunch in the mess.
title: Sainik School Bijapur Teachers' Day 05 Sept 2013,Shri PM Shetty on Pro MB Kudari, Gokak

Ukrainian beekeeper Vasyl Priyatelenko and volunteer Elena Ilienko (Ukraine) at APIMONDIA 2013, by Entomologist in Ukraine
VIDEO LINK = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=78usIGz5dhA

Пчеловод Василий Яковлевич Приятеленко рассказывает об особенностях своей конструкции многокорпусного улья, отличного от всех других конструкций следующим: 1) по наличию металлической верхней планки у всех соторамок, 2) перекрестному расположению соторамок в различных корпусах, 3) высокому корпусу в расплодной части улья, 4) свободному пространству высотой 10 см под нижним корпусом улья, 5) использованию полиэтиленовой пленки или металлической пластины сверху соторамок в верхнем корпусе, 6) снятию всех химических обработок в результате такой конструкции, 7) использование пчелами прополисованной воды внутри улья улучшает здоровье пчелосемьи, 8) перекрестное расположение рамок в корпусах без наличия переходного пространства между корпусами создает единую конструкцию пчелиного гнезда с эффектом пчелиного дупла, 8) уменьшению ройливости пчелосемьи, 9) уменьшению трудозатрат на обслуживание и осмотр пчелосемей.
 
УЛЬИ Василия Яковлевича Приятеленко - оригинальной конструкции.
УЛЬИ Василия Яковлевича Приятеленко  - отличаются 1) наличием рамок с металлической верхней планкой 2) установкой рамок между корпусами без межрамкового пространства 3) установкой рамок в разных корпусах не параллельно, а перекрестно 4) накрытием рамок в верхнем корпусе полиэтиленовой пленкой или металлической пластиной без пчелиного пространства и без утепления 5) наличием пустого 10-см высоты подрамочного пространства в нижнем корпусе улья 6) использованием 2-х или 3-х корпусов для данной конструкции многокорпусного улья 7) созданием более здоровых для развития пчелиной семьи условий в улье, более близких к естественным условиям пчелиного дупла в дереве.
Полное описание ульев и технологии - в книгах и журнальных статьях. опубликованных в Украине и за рубежом (Великобритания).

description:
Hrvatska nadigrala Srbiju!
Hrvatska nogometna reprezentacija slavila je na Maksimiru protiv Srbije s 2:0 u petom kolu skupine A kvalifikacija za odlazak na Svjetsko prvenstvo u Brazilu pogocima Marija Mandžukića (23) i Ivice Olića (37).

Vatreni su se slavljem protiv vrlo jake Srbije dodatno približili na plasmanu na SP, a Srbija je gotovo ostala bez izgleda za odlazak na svjetsku smotru. Hrvatska i dalje s Belgijom predvodi ljestvicu s 13 bodova iz pet susreta, a Srbija je ostala na samo četiri boda.


Tvrd početak

Unatoč najavama, Hrvatska nije uspjela odmah na početku pritisnuti protivnika. Srbija se uspjela oduprijeti i borba se vodila uglavnom na sredini terena. Već u osmoj minuti Srbija je morala promijeniti igrača. Ozlijeđenog napadača Marka Šćepovića zamijenio je Filip Đorđević. 

U 15. minuti Hrvatska je postigla pogodak, ali nažalost iz zaleđa. Nabacivanje s lijeve strane Olić je glavom prebacio loptu, Mandžukić je bio viši od vratara Željka Brkića, ali je bio u nedopuštenom položaju.

U 18. minuti prva prilika Srbije. Aleksandar Kolarov je izvrsno uposlio u našem šesnaestercu Filipa Đuričića, koji se probio do gol crte i pokušao vratiti u sredinu, ali je Darijo Srna izvsrno uklizao i odnio loptu izvan terena. 


Mandžukić iskoristio poklon Srbije

Vatreni su poveli u 23. minuti. Mandžukić je presjekao loptu Kolarova, Rakitić je u prazan uposlio Olića, koji se sjurio prema srpskim vratima, a onda izvrsno uposlio na lijevoj strani Mandžukića, koji je mirno zakucao mrežu za vodstvo Hrvatske.

Nakon primljenog pogotka, Srbija je počela igrati malo otvorenije, no nijedna momčad nije uspjela iskoristiti malo više prostora u sredini.

Olić za veliku prednost

U 36. minuti požutio je Kolarov zbog prekršaja na Mandžukiću 35 metara s desne strane. Vatreni su to iskoristili na najbolji mogući način. Srna je izvrsno nabacio iza leđa srpske obrane na lijevu vratnicu. Najbrži je bio Olić, koji je prsima pospremio loptu u gol i tako povećao prednost na 2:0.

U 40. minuti opasan udarac iz desnog kuta za Srbiju. Lopta je preletjela na lijevu stranu. Tamo je bio najviši Đorđević, ali okružen hrvtskim braničima nije uspio dobro zahvatiti loptu. Dvije minute poslije uslijedila je pogreška hrvatske obrane, ali su Srna i Vedran Ćorluka uspjeli otkloniti opasnost.


Prva opasnija prilika Srbije

Od samog početka drugo poluvrijeme ponudilo je puno sadržajniji nogomet. Prvu priliku imala je Srbija. U 47. minuti Kolarov se probio kroz sredinu, topovski pucao, ali je Stipe Pletikosa izvrsno reagirao i uspio odbiti loptu. Lopta je stigla do Đuričića, koji je pucao, a Đorđević je samo skrenuo loptu loja je završila pored desne vratnice.

Hrvatska je uzvratila samo minutu poslije dalekometnim pokušajem Luke Modrića. U 52. minuti novi solo prodor Modrića, koji je pucao s 20 metara, ali je lopta završila tik pored desne vratnice.

U 60. minuti Mateo Kovačić izvrsno je uposlio Srnu, koji je ubacio u sredinu, ali je Olić bio za korak prekratak. Nakon neuspješnog udarca iz kuta, lopta se ponovno odbila do Rakitića, koji je prevario srpskog braniča i uputio oštar udarac, ali je Brkić zo uspio obraniti.


Pritisak Srbije

U 69. minuti opasan pokušaj Đuričića, a šest minuta poslije nova opasna prilika Srbije. Tadić je ostao sam u našem šesnaestercu, ali je Strinić u posljednji tren uklizao. U 78. minuti najbolja prilika Srbije. Duško Tadić petom je uposlio natrčalog Đuričića čiji je izvrstan udarac Pletikosa odbio, a zatim obranio i pokušaj Đorđevića.

Posljednjih pet minuta Hrvatska čuva veliku prednost. Ipak, u drugoj minuti sudačke nadoknade novi opasan pokušaj Srbije, ali Pletikosa je ponovno izašao kao pobjednik.

U druga dva susreta u skupini Belgija je s 2:0 slavila kod Makedonije, a Wales je s 2:1 slavio kod Škotske. 


Štimac iznenadio debijem Kovačića

Izbornik Igor Štimac iznenadio je uvrštavanjem mladog Matea Kovačića umjesto Ognjena Vukojevića. Štimac se odlučio za sljedeći sastav: Stipe Pletikosa na vratima, u zadnjoj liniji Darijo Srna, Vedran Ćorluka, Josip Šimunić i Ivan Strinić, u vezi Ivan Rakitić, Mateo Kovačić, Luka Modrić i Niko Kranjčar, a u napadu Ivica Olić i Mario Mandžukić.

Izbornik Srbije odlučio se za sljedeće igrače: Željko Brkić, Branislav Ivanović, Neven Subotić, Matija Nastasić, Aleksandar Kolarov, Zoran Tošić, Aleksandar Ignjovski, Ivan Radovanović, Alen Stevanović, Filip Đuričić i Marko Šćepović. 

Vrata maksimirskog stadiona bila su otvorena već u 15 sati, a rasprodani Maksimir je napunilo 35.000 gledatelja sat i pol prije utakmice. Duž sve četiri maksimirske tribine izvješeni su transparenti podrške hrvatskoj reprezentaciji iz svih hrvatskih gradova, kao i gradova iz susjedne BiH.
title: Hrvatska-Srbija 2:0  22.3.2013. (sažetak CRO-SRB 2:0)

description:
Brief flight of my Syma S031G R/C Coaxial Helicopter (new vers. with Li:Po battery); aerial videography done with my Rechargeable Mini Keychain Video Recorder affixed to the heli's canopy.
 
Flight took place in a socker field at Celebration Park in Federal Way WA. USA on 06-25-14 (or, "2014 25 Jun." or even, "June 25, Twenty Stick-Pile-of-Crossed-Busted-Sticks if you prefer).
 
Weather conditions at flight time were cloudy, temperature of 61°F (16.1°C), and winds out of the N at 3mph (2.595kts, 4.83kph).
 
The heli experienced mid-air blade strike, breaking off one of the main rotor blades, which is why this flight is so brief.
 
I highly suspect that the heli experienced a sudden downdraft, causing one of the lower rotor blades to strike the camera (thus neutralising it) and bounce upward into the path of the counterrotating upper blades which subsequently caused it to strike one of the upper blades and thus become destroyed.
I have already ordered replacement main rotor blades, which should arrive here in very early-July 2014, after which my flights can resume.
 
More info. about the Rechargeable Mini Keychain Video Recorder on my website in its eval. at http://ledmuseum.candlepower.us/46/vcamera.htm and about my Syma S031G R/C Coaxial Helicopter (new vers. with Li:Po battery) at http://ledmuseum.candlepower.us/46/syma0312.htm

description:
Celtic   1 - 1   Rangers

Rangers retained their seven-point lead in the Scottish Premier League after a controversial backs-to-the-wall draw against second-top city rivals Celtic.

Celtic were left angered when Marc-Antoine Fortune had a goal chopped off for a foul on keeper Allan McGregor.

And Rangers' Kyle Lafferty was fortunate not to be sent off for a lunging challenge on Andreas Hinkel.

Scott McDonald headed Celtic into a deserved lead after 79 minutes, but Lee McCulloch matched that seconds later.

It had been Rangers' first effort on target but secured a draw that will leave the blue half of Glasgow the happier, retaining a cushion over a Celtic side who have a game in hand.

Celtic manager Tony Mowbray had sprung a surprise ahead of kick-off by dropping striker McDonald and starting Fortune up front along with Georgios Samaras.

Stephen McManus was the man to lose out in central defence following the return from suspension of Gary Caldwell.

While Mowbray obviously thought those changes strengthened his side, Rangers counterpart Walter Smith's changes were required to cover for two of his top performers of recent weeks.

Smith showed faith in 18-year-old Danny Wilson, who started in central defence in place of Madjid Bougherra, who had joined Algeria's African Cup of Nations squad.

Steven Whittaker came into midfield in the absence of the suspended Kenny Miller, with Lafferty moving up front to partner Kris Boyd.

Re-jigged Rangers started on the front foot, but Celtic's defence stood firm as the visitors played pinball with a series of attempted efforts that were blocked outside the penalty box.

Rangers' hopes suffered a blow after 11 minutes, when Nacho Novo picked up an injury and was replaced with the more defensively-minded Maurice Edu.

And, as the game settled, it was the home side who were controlling possession, with the Rangers defence increasingly stretched and their challenges becoming increasingly desperate.

It seemed only a matter of time before Celtic made the breakthrough and it looked like they had done just that after 19 minutes when Fortune headed home from five yards.

However, referee Steve Conroy ruled that the striker had led with the arm as he challenged McGregor to a miss-hit McGeady volley that flew high into the air.

Conroy appeared to have got that call right despite the resulting anger from the home support, but he was too lenient 11 minutes later when only producing a yellow card after Lafferty lunged dangerously, studs-first into Hinkel's shin.

Celtic's speed and movement was a delight to watch, but Rangers' doggedness was denying them threats on goal until a fine Hinkel cross was met by the head of Barry Robson and looped from 15 yards off the face of the crossbar.

Samaras ought to have given Celtic the lead two minutes before half-time, breaking through the challenge of Wilson but steering his drive from the edge of the box wide of the far post.

The Greek striker and McGeady both squandered chances early in the second half despite Rangers showing more attacking intention.

Fortune pounced on an Edu mistake to tee up McGeady in the clear on the edge of the box, but the winger fired high over the crossbar.

A 16-yard snap shot on the turn from Celtic substitute McDonald almost squirmed under McGregor.

However, the Australian striker did make the breakthrough after 79 minutes, stealing in behind his marker to head home from five yards after a cross from McGeady, who had teased his way past two defenders.

The lead only lasted two minutes, McCulloch rising above Caldwell 12 yards out to powerfully head home a Steven Davis corner.

McGregor prevented Celtic retaking the lead after 84 minutes, turning a curling 20-yard drive from Samaras brilliantly over the crossbar with his outstretched hand.

Celtic manager Tony Mowbray:
"We played on the front foot. We pushed them back.

"I think we felt we had done enough to come away with three points.

"I thought the referee had a good game. He obviously saw a free kick against Fortune and gave it. You have to abide by the decisions.

"I am trying to build a team not just to win the league this season but for the next four or five years and hopefully our brand of football will do that in the long run."

Rangers manager Walter Smith:
"We were very fortunate to get a draw. Celtic started the better side.

"Celtic played very well. It was a tough afternoon for a lot of our boys.

"I felt the second half we did a little bit better.

"We are delighted to have got a point from a game we should not have. We were not with the pace of the game at all."
title: YNWA - Celtic v. Rangers - 03 Jan 2010

description:
It was said she'd unlikely make it, but Stephanie Limpscomb will soon be celebrating her 23rd birthday and doing it cancer-free.
 
It was said she'd unlikely make it, but Stephanie Lipscomb will soon be celebrating her 23rd birthday and doing it cancer-free.

 At age 20, her doctors found a rare type of tumor in her brain and the prognosis was that she'd only be able to survive for about two more years. 

That was before the option of an experimental treatment that utilizes the poliovirus was available. 

After surgery, radiation and chemotherapy failed to keep the tumor from returning, Stephanie was presented with the alternative method. 

Doctors were clear that she would be injected with a version of the potentially deadly virus, a procedure that had never been tried on humans before and that it was risky.  

She didn't hesitate to say yes to the opportunity. 

Clearly, that was the right answer as it successfully killed off the tumor. Brain scans show only a bit of scar tissue where the growth once was. 

 Doctors at Duke University Medical Center hope to treat more patients using the technique. 

They've done several already, and have seen them prove to be successful treatments.
title: College Student's Brain Tumor Knocked Out by Poliovirus

The panda also known as the giant panda to distinguish it from the unrelated red panda, is a bear native to south central China. It is easily recognized by the large, distinctive black patches around its eyes, over the ears, and across its round body. The giant panda lives in a few mountain ranges in central China, mainly in Sichuan province, but also in the Shaanxi and Gansu provinces.
The giant panda has a body shape typical of bears. It has black fur on its ears, eye patches, muzzle, legs, arms and shoulders. The rest of the animal's coat is white. Although scientists do not know why these unusual bears are black and white, speculation suggests that the bold colouring provides effective camouflage in their shade-dappled snowy and rocky habitat.
In the wild, the giant panda is a terrestrial animal and primarily spends its life roaming and feeding in the bamboo forests of the Qinling Mountains and in the hilly Sichuan Province. Giant pandas are generally solitary, and each adult has a defined territory, and a female is not tolerant of other females in her range.
Despite its taxonomic classification as a carnivore, the giant panda's diet is primarily herbivorous, consisting almost exclusively of bamboo. Pandas are born with sterile intestines, and require bacteria obtained from their mother's faeces to digest vegetation. However, the giant panda still has the digestive system of a carnivore, as well as carnivore-specific genes, and thus derives little energy and little protein from consumption of bamboo. Its ability to digest cellulose is ascribed to the microbes in its gut. The giant panda is a "highly specialized" animal with "unique adaptations", and has lived in bamboo forests for millions of years
Giant pandas reach sexual maturity between the ages of four and eight, and may be reproductive until age The mating season is between March and May, when a female goes into oestrus, which lasts for two or three days and only occurs once a year. When mating, the female is in a crouching, head-down position as the male mounts her from behind. Copulation time is short, ranging from 30 seconds to five minutes, but the male may mount her repeatedly to ensure successful fertilization. The gestation period ranges from 95 to 160 days.
title: Panda Showing gymnastics ! パンダ目を表示し体操

description:
Fr. Marek instructs students about iconography in his first of two summer classes being held at St. Emilian's Byzantine Catholic Church in Brunswick, Ohio.  For an entire week, students, who gathered from around the country, attend classes to be introduced to the ancient art of "writing icons".  Unlike religious paintings that tell a story, an icon is theology in color.

Here, we see the students follow master iconographer, Father Marek's example in writing the icon of Saint Nicholas of Myra, the real Santa Claus.  Saint Nicholas not only cared for the poor, but intervened on behalf of those slated for capital punishment and defended the Christian faith at the First Ecumenical Council of Nicaea.

At the end of the week long class, the students will join father in having their icons blessed at the Divine Liturgy.  They will then take them home for devotional purposes.

Icons are not objects of worship.

eul sur le sable, les yeux dans l'eau... Voici Paul. A 31 ans, cet expatrié Français à Singapour est le nouveau Bachelor de NT1. Beau, sportif, gentil et intelligent, c'est le garçon idéal à en croire le portrait dressé par la chaine. Qui produit une vidéo de présentation multipliant les clichés.

On découvre d'abord Paul, les yeux dans le vague, observant la beauté des flots. Puis, il se retrouve face caméra... sous la douche, dans un remake des publicités pour le savon. Suivent une succession de plans rapprochés pour découvrir le sourire (crispé) du beau Paul.

Le nouvel homme sandwich à consommer sur place par les prétendantes de NT1 a de nouveaux atouts. A la tête d'une société de fusion-acquisition avec 5 autres associés, Paul vit une vie de rêve. Quand il ne travaille pas, ce fêtard assumé passe des week-ends en toute décontraction à Bali. Sportif, ce grand garçon pratique à haut niveau le rugby, avec d'autres expatriés.

Dans le portrait, vient le tour d'une des sœurs de Paul, qui dit tout le bien qu'elle pense de son frère dans un murmure, comme pourrait le faire Isabelle Adjani ou Carla Bruni.

description:
U.S. health officials are debating to approve trials for a novel in vitro fertilization technique which uses DNA from three people to eliminate debilitating disease.

Defective mitochondrial DNA from the mother's egg can lead to muscle weakness, and even heart and respiratory failures in the offspring.

The Food and Drug Administration conducted a review on this procedure which is expected to circumvent life-threatening mitochondrial diseases by replacing the mother's defective mitochondrial DNA with a 'second' mother's.

Critics of this technique argue that this puts us on a slippery slope towards making 'designer babies.'

"Where we get into the sticky part is, what if you get past transplanting batteries and start to say, 'While we're at it, why don't we make you taller, stronger, faster or smarter?'" Art Caplan, the director of medical ethics at New York University's Langone Medical Center, said in a CNN report.

Britain became the first country to allow this procedure in June. It is estimated that one in 6,500 babies in the UK is born with mitochondrial disorder each year.
title: FDA review three-parent fertilization procedure

description:
Watch more Card Flourishes & Sleight of Hand videos: http://www.howcast.com/videos/515125-How-to-Do-a-Thumb-Cut-Magic-Card-Flourishes

Learn how to do a one-handed shuffle from magician Michael Patrick in this Howcast card flourish tutorial.


Hi. I'm Mike Patrick and this is how to do a one-handed shuffle. It looks like this. You take the cards and shuffle them with one hand like this. The grip is a little bit unusual. You have three fingers on one end of the deck and your pinky and thumb on the other side. So, if I remove the deck, it's like this and if I place the deck back it's around here. What you're going to do is divide approximately, and you want this to be relatively exact, you want to get half the deck to break off with your thumb. I lift up with my thumb here. These two fingers let go let go at this point. I'm going to move my thumb counterclockwise, pivoting along the index finger and this packet is going to move clockwise. This is what it's going to look like. These two move at the same rate until they're here. 

The two outer fingers now regroup this edge and pull it so that they are even with each other. It's a very slight adjustment when this happens, about a quarter of an inch, depending on your hand size. You then take the two back portions and you shuffle those together with even pressure from your thumb. This is going to take the most work. One more time, you have the pinky here and the thumb. You break upwards with your thumb. Your fingers move out of the way. It pivots around the index finger so they swirl on opposite directions. I reapply those two fingers, aligning the packets. And now I place those together and I cause them to weave at an angle. So now I should have sort of a V from my perspective. Now the cards are ready to be bridged. I turn them over. 

I apply pressure like in a normal shuffle and I let go of them. They will fall over the floor when you try to do this. It's unavoidable but eventually you can use your hand or cradle if you feel more comfortable. But eventually over time you should just be able to do it in the air like this. I'll go over it really slowly one more time. The pinky is here towards this pip on that side. The thumb breaks the packet. I remove these fingers and I pivot this across. They're aligned with each other. These cards get farrowed the other cards and then I turn over and I shuffle them like this. Here's one quick variation that I can show you that I do. You can cut off about a third of the deck. If you do that, when these cards are in this orientation you can use your index finger to move this packet forward so this just pivots along these, goes into this hand, and you do a thumb cut so your thumb comes over. This opens up. And you can shuffle these into each other. This is going like this. And then you close. You see that in speed it looks like this. And that is how to do a one-handed shuffle.
title: How to Do a One-Handed Shuffle | Magic Card Flourishes

This interview-led documentary style program explains what psychometric testing is and why it's used, the various types of psychometric tests candidates might encounter, how to prepare for tests, and the advantages and disadvantages of psychometric testing.

Those interviewed for the program include Mandy Jones, careers consultant at Cardiff University, clinical psychologist Dr Simon Kensella, Melissa Martin, director of the Clarity Group, Becky Bevans, HR consultant for Pardos Bevans Consulting, and Prue Laurence, consulting psychologist and director of Psylutions. Suited to senior secondary and TAFE for those seeking employment or a change of career, it is also a great resource in the fields of psychology, business studies and career counselling.

description:
George London has been a master keyboardist and entertainer for most of his life.  When he was a boy in London, England he was in a choir that performed at a Royal Command Performance at the Albert Hall with Princess Elizabeth, Princes Margaret and the Queen Mother in attendance.  He has been in various bands in England and Sydney Australia.  He formed the George London Jazz Trio many decades ago and it played to packed houses at various venues all the time.  

Genial in nature, if you are invited to George's home you are immediately taken to his music room and treated to the latest sounds he has been working on.  He will amaze you with his wizardry on the keyboard.  His keyboards look like they could be the instrument panel on a 747 jet aircraft - buttons, switches and lights everywhere you look.  His arms flail as he prepares the keyboard to play, flipping switches here and there, and pressing button after button until the tone of the keyboard will be just right.  The lights dance over the entire surface of the keyboard and when everything is just right he presses the "GO" button.  You are treated to a musical fantasy of songs you have probably heard throughout your life but this time they are being played by the masterful hands of George as he performs a concert just for you. 

George has produced many CDs which he sells when he performs at social clubs and RSLs all around the Shoalhaven area.  "Let Me Entertain You" is his calling card and for those who attend his performances he will not disappoint.
title: George London:  Master Keyboardist

description:
Pound 4 pound Official Hand Wrap

http://www.pound4poundflorida.com

In this video we demonstrate how to wrap your hands for Boxing, Kickboxing and Muay Thai. Hand wrapping helps support your wrist and knuckles so that you can get the most out of your training or workout without injury.
To wrap your hands start  with the loop around your thumb and start wrapping around the back of the wrist. Come underneath the wrist 3 times. Next, circle around the wrist and then wrap around the thumb to protect the joint then once again around the wrist. 
Go between each finger starting with the pinky and work back towards the index finger.

Go up to the knuckles along the back of the hand. Wrap around the knuckles 2 to 3 times. Finish by making an X on the back of the hand as you go back down to the wrist.

Finish by wrapping around the wrist and securing.

A lesson that I learned while making stickers was that it was easier to make 4 or 5 of the same sticker in not much more time than one.  Here is the reason why.  Most of your time spent is setting things up or getting the ball rolling.  Now this works for a lot of things and not just stickers.

I have noticed that it is much easier and more effective for me to do the same task multiple times versus completing a project from start to end.

So this is a video project looks like broken down using Chunking. 

1. First step is creating the video.  Instead of setting up and creating one video I will create a series of videos.  Normally it is a weeks worth of content.  By doing this I have saved time setting up and most importantly I tend to get into a grove of making the videos. 

2.  Next I will edit all the videos in the same session.  Here again save time by using a template for first one and just going through the complete series of videos.

3.  Then on to uploading.  Here again by doing them all together I am able to be more effective in my efforts and saving time over the series of videos.  If I don't want to release them all on the same day I will have them unlisted until I am ready.

You can see how if you just did one video at a time you wouldn't be as effective.  I also like to do it this way because it gives me more flexibility of when I do things.
title: How to Be More Effective Using Chunking

description:
August 2012 brought some very hot and humid conditions to the Santa Clarita and Antelope Valleys in Southern California...  This tropical air comes up from the southest each summer creating ideal conditions for afternoon thunderstorm formation over the desert areas. In these sequences, we can see these clouds forming and spreading - some reaching into the upper troposphere where they fan out into the classic anvil shape of Cumulonimbus. As the storms mature and then finally collapse, the magic of timelapse photography reveals some very interesting atmospheric movement - with cloud remnants twisting and swirling in weird ways.

These scenes were filmed with tripod-mounted Canon 5DMk2 and SX10-is digital cameras.

Alligator hatchlings are extremely vulnerable to attacks from birds. Not just many large wadding birds like the grey heron feed on newly hatched alligators but birds of prey like large owls prey on young alligators too. But the Female alligator will protect its hatchlings for the first year, making it difficult for any bird to approach. Newborn alligators don't need to feed right away, because they still have enough yolk from their egg to provide for the needed nutrition. Most hatchlings will start feeding within the next two weeks after birth and prey on insects, invertebrates, small fish, frogs, mice and anything else they can catch and swallow. The hatching of american alligator was filmed by Heiko Kiera in 2010.
title: Predators of Alligators 0401 - Birds - Dangerous Animals

Dae Jang Geum (literally The Great Jang Geum) is a 2003 epic South Korean television series directed by Lee Byung Hoon and produced by MBC. Starring Lee Young Ae, it tells the tale of an orphaned kitchen cook who went on to become the king's first female physician. In a time when women held little influence in society, young apprentice cook Jang Geum strives to learn the secrets of Korean cooking and medicine in order to cure the King of his various ailments. Produced for $15 million, the show received as much as 57% of viewers in South Korea and has pulled in $40 million worldwide since it first aired in 2003.

It is based on the true story of Jang-geum, the first female royal physician of the Joseon Dynasty. The main themes are her perseverance and the portrayal of traditional Korean culture, including Korean royal court cuisine and traditional medicine.

description:
Arizer Extreme Q 4.0 Medical Marijuana Herbal Vaporizer Review

Arizer Extreme Q 4.0 Medical Marijuana Herbal Vaporizer Review

Arizer Extreme Q 4.0 Medical Marijuana Herbal Vaporizer Review

Arizer Extreme Q 4.0 Medical Marijuana Herbal Vaporizer Review

The Extreme-Q is a dual purpose vaporizer, meaning it can be used with a whip (a long tube) or with a big bag (balloon style).

The main things I like about this device are that it looks cool, it has a remote control, and it has a lot of functions. A couple of things that bug me a tiny bit are the glass parts that get hot when you're vaping, cus I almost burned myself once, and that you need to stir around the herbs a few times to ensure it's getting evenly vaped. Not a huge deal just a minor annoyance.

The other thing that bugs me a little bit is having to keep your finger on the end of the mouthpiece to keep the vapor from coming out. I guess I might be spoiled from the Volcano, which has built-in valves in each balloon that automatically keep them sealed, but I'm sure if you vape often you'll get a little annoyed at that too. This requirement is not specific to the Extreme-Q though, most whip style vaporizers work the same way.

Overall this is a pretty cool vape and lots of people love it. If you're mainly looking for a good balloon-style vaporizer I still think the Volcano is worth the extra cost. The V is really in a league of it's own, but for half the price the Extreme-Q does the job pretty well.

VapeRating: 85/100
title: Arizer Extreme Q 4.0 Medical Marijuana Herbal Vaporizer Review

description:
View Full Recipe At:
http://www.happivore.com/recipe/chipotles-sofritas-tacos/

A homemade rendition of the Chipotle classic. Tofu is braised with tomato, chilies, and a wicked blend of spices before being scooped onto soft tortillas and topped with guacamole.

Time: 35 minutes
Makes: 8 tacos
Cost per taco: $1.90
INGREDIENTS
• 1 package firm tofu (14 or 16 oz)
• 1 tablespoon olive oil
• 1 can black beans
• 1 can corn
• 8 large flour tortillas
• 2 avocados

SOFRITA SAUCE

• 1 tomato
• 1 small yellow onion
• 1 red bell pepper
• 1 chipotle pepper
• 1 cup fresh cilantro
• 3 large cloves garlic
• juice from ½ a lime
• 1 teaspoon oregano
• 1 teaspoon coriander
• 1 teaspoon salt
• 2 teaspoons ground chili pepper (use two different kinds, found in the Mexican section of grocery stores)
• black pepper to taste

INSTRUCTIONS

1. Drain tofu by placing on a paper towel, and setting a heavy plate on top for 15 minutes.
2. Blend all the sofrito sauce ingredients together in a blender or food processor for about a minute, or until it looks like salsa.
3. Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat. Crumble tofu into a bowl with your hands, then drop it into the pan. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring once or twice, to lightly brown. 
4. Pour 1½ cups of the sofrito sauce onto the tofu. Add black beans and corn. Stir well to mix, then lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes. 
5. Lightly toast the tortillas. Spoon the sofritas onto the tortillas, then top with avocado and fresh cilantro.
title: Happivore - Chipotle's Sofritas Taco Recipe (Vegan)

Two FEMEN activists ripped off their tops on Wednesday in front of Berlin's historic Victory Column in an attempt to protest before US President Barack Obama's car as he drove from Schloss Bellevue to the Chancellery during his visit to Germany's capital. The two women waited patiently on the pavement surrounded by police until their phones went off, indicating it was time for them to start.

Police became privy to the fact that there were two FEMEN members about to protest and acted as though Obama's car were arriving, although his route had been changed, and the two girls ended up protesting missing the motorcade.

Nevertheless a crowd of 30 people and more than 50 police officers looked on as the topless girls cried out "Free our sisters!" before police dragged them kicking and screaming into a waiting police van, where they were then held for at least 30 minutes without driving away. One of the activists, a green-haired 22-year-old who goes by the name 'Debbie' left a police officer screaming "She bit me", as police attempted to apprehend the two girls.

FEMEN's scream to "Free our sisters" was in regard to the four FEMEN activists who have been imprisoned in Tunisia for over four months. FEMEN leader Inna Shevchenko has said that if the FEMEN activists were not released following their trial, further protests would be held to exert international pressure for their release.
title: Germany: "Free our sisters!" cries FEMEN missing Obama's motorcade

Chiedo una penna al secondino
io il brigatista, il dissociato
la Chiesa di San Bellarmino
torna alla mente l'uomo accasciato.

Poi quel ragazzo quasi un cristallo
in faccia al mondo volle pregare
disse perdono come uno sparo
e il nostro cuore iniziò a sanguinare.

E sai stasera amore la notte trema perché
mi stordisce il pensiero violentissimo e guerriero 
del perdono per Vittorio Bachelet
e sai stasera dolore c'è una domanda per te
è l'abisso del timore, fa paura più del male 
e per questo ora cara scrivo a te
ma sai stasera amore tremo perché.

Voglio pregare per chi ha colpito
per chi ha colpito il mio papà
e se giustizia invocherò
mai la vendetta pronuncerò.

Sapessi amore quante sere
ho ripetuto quelle parole
guardo le stelle oltre le sbarre
c'è il tuo profumo che mi rincorre.

E sai stasera amore la notte brilla perché
mi ha incantato il pensiero tenerissimo e guerriero
del perdono per Vittorio Bachelet
e sai stasera dolore c'è meno posto per te
è l'abisso dell'amore, fa paura più del male 
e per questo ora cara scrivo a te.
E sai stasera amore la vita nasce perché

description:
Watch the great swimmers' hands, and you'll see how soft they are when they swim.   They're always searching to find that constant connection with the water.


Why Do It:
Sculling in all directions helps you develop a better feel for the water.  Strapless sculling, or using paddles that have limited connection to the hands, helps you feel the press of the scull, while still focusing on having the palms turned in the correct direction.

How to Do It:
1.  Start with you feet behind you, on your back.
2.  Start to scull with your fingertips facing UP.  If you do this right, you should move backward.
3.  Now simply turn the fingertips DOWN.  If you do this right, you should move forward, toward the feet.
4.  Remember:  This isn't pulling.  Don't sweep your hands around like this swimmer is doing.
5.  Sweep back and forth with the hands while keeping the shoulders and elbows as still as possible.

How to Do It Really Well (the Fine Points):
Remain completely still with everything except the lower arm.  Keep the body steady, the arms, the head... remain like a rock except for the lower arms and hands.  If you have to kick to keep the feet up, sometimes a pull buoy can help further isolate what you're focusing on.
title: All Strokes - Trailing-Hands Sculling

description: Beautiful classic tune with a soaring tonality on pipes not heard in the minor key versions of other instruments. Played at JFK graveside and Queen Mother's funeral. From the stereo vinyl album "Scots Guards Pipes and Drums - Marches," one of the only recordings I know much before the mid to late 60's with excellent rock-steady tuning and light, intricate playing by a large band. Uses the old melodic style drumming from before the Alex Duthart era, pipe pitch much lower than today. You have to listen through online compression, heavily played vinyl and 50's hi-fi-stereo engineering, but it's a very powerful band sound. Mostly march-strathspey-reel-6/8 and street- & slow march sets. The recording was still being sold into the 1970's but I've never seen a CD print.
title: Mist-Covered Mountains, Scots Guards 1950

description:
Efforts by U.S. intelligence officials to track American and European-born fighters who travel to the Middle East to join Islamic extremist groups like ISIS have been complicated by different approaches to sharing information and homeland security from their European counterparts, according to a published report. 

The Wall Street Journal reports that U.S. officials are struggling to ascertain the movements of suspected extremists once they enter certain European countries. The gaps are occurring despite the fact that the U.S. and several European security services have developed close intelligence links, with intelligence from both sides of the Atlantic buttressing terror watch lists kept by U.S. officials, such as the no-fly list. 

According to the Journal, a particular cause for concern among U.S. intelligence officials is a series of anti-terror proposals made last week by British Prime Minister David Cameron, most notably to revoke the passports of British nationals who have traveled to fight for ISIS. The British proposal reportedly has been greeted warily by U.S. counter-terrorism officials, who say that any move to confiscate passports could prevent people who have traveled to Syria and Iraq from speaking to authorities and providing intelligence about what is happening there. 

Apparently buttressing the U.S. officials' concerns, a report in The Times of London last week suggested that up to 30 British-born ISIS fighters have been disgusted by the militants' brutal tactics and wish to return home, but are fearful of doing so due to the punitive measures advocated by Cameron. 

Meanwhile, President Obama is scheduled to meet with congressional leaders Tuesday afternoon to discuss his plan to combat the ISIS threat. Few details of Obama's plan have been revealed ahead of a scheduled Wednesday address to the nation, though the New York Times reported Monday that the White House was in the process of planning a three-phase campaign that some Pentagon officials believe would take at least three years to fully execute. 

The U.S. has already launched close to 150 airstrikes against ISIS in Iraq, and The Times reported that the final phase of the campaign would call for the extension of airstrikes into Syria, where ISIS has its home base. 

The Obama administration is also bringing pressure on allies to swing firmly behind action against ISIS. Secretary of State John Kerry is scheduled to travel to to Saudi Arabia and Jordan to meet with Mideast leaders and gauge their level of commitment to a growing worldwide coalition. The Associated Press reported that Kerry pressed a core group of 10 countries  to form a loose coalition to go after last week's NATO summit. Along with the United States, the coalition comprises the United Kingdom, France, Australia, Germany, Canada, Turkey, Italy, Poland and Denmark.

If there is a more colorful Celosia, it's hard to imagine how! 'China Town' has won Europe's top honor for seeds -- the Fleuroselect Quality Mark -- and now it's set to conquer America! These brilliant red blooms on red stems atop dark, deep purple leaves are so neon-bright they look freshly painted, yet they last from early summer into autumn on plants that are quite easy to grow!
The seeds sprout in spring quite plain, with green leaves and nothing much to say for themselves. But as the warm weather of summer arrives and the buds begin to set, many things happen at once. The green vanishes in favor of a rich smoldering purple hue. The flowering stems turn red. And the buds burst into brilliant Chinese-lacquer red! Although 'China Town' only reaches 14 to 16 inches high and 8 inches wide, even a small planting makes a huge impact.
title: Celosia China Town
